{"word":"G609 - ἀποκόπτω - apokóptō - ap-ok-op'-to - Cut off","slug":"G609","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀποκόπτω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>apokóptō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ap-ok-op'-to"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cut off"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03C0;&#x03BF;&#x03BA;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03C4;&#x03C9; - apokopto&#x0304;</b> - <i>ap-ok-op'-to</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G575\">G575</a> and <a href=\"#/G2875\">G2875</a>; to <i>amputate</i>; reflexively (by irony) to <i>mutilate</i> (the privy parts): - cut off. Compare <a href=\"#/G2699\">G2699</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1464\">G1464</a>, <a href=\"#/G1465\">G1465</a>, <a href=\"#/G1581\">G1581</a>, <a href=\"#/G2870\">G2870</a>, <a href=\"#/G2875\">G2875</a>"}]}